programme.title: Granny's Spring Tonic
programme.desc: Miss Hathaway's bank protegee, Gloria, is a sultry gold-digger who begins to eye up Jed and his $34 million.

programme.title: The Grunion Hunt Mystery
programme.desc: Mickey's plan for a grunion hunt with Pat are foiled by a strange character.

programme.title: The Case of the Impromptu Performance
programme.desc: A condemned man scheduled to hang the next day uses his last request to ask Sherlock Holmes to prove his innocence.

programme.title: Dr. Impossible
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Morrison Story
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: Gets a Bachelor Apartment
programme.desc: A clerk named Stanley finds himself embroiled in the chaotic ongoings of New York City tourists inside an upscale hotel.

programme.title: No Partiality
programme.desc: In a move towards equal treatment, both Betty and Kathy get to invite a boy to dinner. Turns out - they want to ask the same boy!

programme.title: Million Dollar Kid (1944)
programme.desc: When the East Side Kids tangle with some West Side Crooks, it's a jillion dollar holler! The gang is befriended by a millionaire after saving him from a mugging, but when they realize the man’s son was one of the criminals, they set out to reform him. Leo Gorcey and Huntz Hall star as Muggs and Glimpy, ganging up on the toughest guys in town! This really is the East Side Kids’ fight of fights!

programme.title: Submarine Alert
programme.desc: Looking to pay for his young ward's operation, a radio engineer falls prey to a Nazi spy ring when he loses his job.

programme.title: Wild Guitar
programme.desc: It's an Elvis movie without Elvis! Cult director Ray Dennis Steckler (The Thrill Killers) made his directorial debut with Wild Guitar, a cheesy, campy, surprisingly entertaining musical drama starring Arch Hall Jr. as Bud Eagle, a naïve singer who gets a shot at the big time. Steckler not only directed this frenzy of musical action, but also appears as a menacing thug working for record company crooks. Co-written and produced by Hall's father, Arch Hall Sr., (who should be known as the godfather of exploitation for films like The Chopper and The Sadist) this one really rocks!

programme.title: At War with the Army (1950)
programme.desc: It's Jerry Lewis and Dean Martin in their first staring vehicle! Lewis plays Alvin Korwin, a bumbler who goes from one disaster to the next, while the suave Sgt. Vic Puccinelli (Martin) tries to keep him out of trouble. Director Hal Walker, who had previously worked with the team of Bob Hope and Bing Crosby, found comedy gold in Martin and Lewis. Songs include 'You And Your Beautiful Eyes', and 'Tonda Wanda Hoy'. For trivia buffs, throughout the film, Lewis gives a Boy Scout salute instead of an Army salute.

programme.title: The Life of Christ - Vol. 1
programme.desc: A television mini-series told the life of Christ in a version of the typical Hollywood serial film.

programme.title: Let's Get Tough (1942)
programme.desc: You may think you’ve seen everything, but you never saw The East Side Kids take on a gang of Japanese spies! Riled by the attack on Pearl Harbor, the boys (Leo Gorcey, Huntz Hall, and the rest) discover a real group of Japanese spies in their neighborhood. Are the East Siders bright enough to expose them? Sure they are! It’s good old American propaganda at its finest!

programme.title: Sherlock Holmes: The Woman In Green (1945)
programme.desc: Sherlock Holmes gets the call when several young women turn up dead in London. The only common clue is that each corpse is missing a finger. Holmes suspects a diabolical plot hatched by his arch enemy Moriarty, but the trail leads him to a society of hypnotists, and a mysterious woman. Is she a temptress of pleasure ­ or mistress of murder? Basil Rathbone and Nigel Bruce reprise their roles as Holmes and Dr. Watson, while Henry Daniell and Hillary Brooke are on hand as Moriarty and the alluring woman of the title!

programme.title: Invaders From Space
programme.desc: The evil salamander men have poisoned Earth with a plague, and it is up to Starman (Ken Utsui) to save mankind. But who are these salamander men, and why do they want to destroy us? It's hard to say, but you'll have fun watching them try.

programme.title: Broadway Jungle
programme.desc: A fledgling Hollywood director, desperate for cash to pay his rent, enlists local gangsters to help him produce his next great film. Murder, mayhem, seduction, and simpering starlets ensue.

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 3
programme.desc: Carol hosts Jonathan Winters and Eddie Albert along with a variety of skits.

programme.title: Season 18 Episode 195
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: Curse of Bigfoot (1975)
programme.desc: Beware - not of Bigfoot, but of this movie! A group of high school kids go exploring in a cave and stumble upon a mummy, but when they remove it, the nasty old thing comes to life and starts terrorizing their small California town! If this doesn't look exactly like a 1970s movie, that's because producer/director Dave Flocker shot most of it in 1958 as Teenagers Battle the Thing. Bigfoot enthusiasts might be appalled, but lovers of schlock might find this feature to be just what they need!

programme.title: King of the Zombies
programme.desc: Blood­chilling revelations of the weird cult that practices its black magic in the impenetrable jungles of Central America! Dick Purcell, Joan Woodbury, Mantan Moreland, and Henry Victor star in this comedy chiller from Monogram, directed by Jean Yarbrough ( House of Horrors, The Brute Man). It’s all about a trio of plane crash survivors who take refuge in a mansion, where a sinister doctor is conducting zombie experiments. If you can sit through this spine­tingling carnival of shrieks and howls without getting the thrill of a lifetime...you must belong to the living dead!

programme.title: Creature from the Haunted Sea (1961)
programme.desc: Here’s another Roger Corman classic from the golden age of Drive-In schlock! In this spoof of horror and spy thrillers, American gangster Renzo Capetto (Anthony Carbone) decides to kill members of his bungling crew and blame their deaths on a legendary sea creature. What he doesn’t know is that the creature is actually out there!

programme.title: The Sadist
programme.desc: Written and directed by James Landis, this thriller loosely follows the story of the killing spree of Charles Starkweather (later films Badlands, 1973, and Natural Born Killers, 1994, were also based on Starkweather’s tale). Starring Arch Hall, Jr. The Sadist begins with three high school teachers driving through California. Unfortunately, their car breaks down in an abandoned area, where they experience a run in with a bloodthirsty sadist and his girlfriend. A truly terrifying experience, this film will have you on the edge of your seat from start to finish!

programme.title: Chair (1957)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big Break (1953)
programme.desc: Friday leads a team in a raid on the house of a very dangerous armed robber, which results in a bloody shootout.

programme.title: Brainwave (1959)
programme.desc: While aboard a United States ship in Japanese waters during World War II, a hospital corpsman is forced to perform surgery on a critically injured Captain Fielding. A doctor on another ship guides the hospital corpsman through the radio.

programme.title: The Man Below (1959)
programme.desc: Mike believes the man who was recently pushed into a well is the same man he was hired to prove is still alive. To prove that this is the right man, Mike must convince miners that the man is still alive, since no one is willing to risk their life rescuing a corpse.

programme.title: Escape to Ponderosa
programme.desc: Ben helps three deserters, escaped from an Army stockade. Learning what they had to deal with, Ben promises to share the truth with his friend who is in charge of the fort.

programme.title: Jed Pays His Income Tax
programme.desc: Granny chases away an IRS agent.

programme.title: The Other Woman
programme.desc: Mickey showcases some home movies which include one with an incriminating scene of his boss.

programme.title: The Case of the Baker Street Bachelors
programme.desc: A political leader is being blackmailed, and to find the blackmailers, Holmes and Watson join a lonely hearts club. Little did thay know things would go awry as Holmes ending up getting arrested.

programme.title: Break Through the Bars
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Poison Ivy Story
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: and the Blonde Bandit
programme.desc: When Stanley arrives late for his date with Celia, he tells her he was held hostage by a group of robbers.

programme.title: Close Decision
programme.desc: Margaret insists that Bud miss his baseball game in order to stop slacking on his chores.

programme.title: The Brave One
programme.desc: A young Mexican boy tirelessly tries to save his pet bull from death at the hands of a celebrated matador.

programme.title: Adventures of Gallant Bess (1948)
programme.desc: As cowboy Ted Daniels, Cameron Mitchell (Carousel) shares the screen with a magnificent wild horse named Gallant Bess. Ted tames, trains and keeps Bess for himself, but after Ted is gravely injured in a fixed rodeo, Bess is stolen away from him and forced to join a cruel traveling carnival. This fast-paced western is from director Lew Landers (The Adventures of Rin Tin Tin).

programme.title: Son of Monte Cristo (1940)
programme.desc: Louis Hayward, Joan Bennett and George Sanders headline this Oscar-nominated adventure tale set in the Balkans. Revered director Rowland V. Lee (Son of Frankenstein, Tower of London) keeps the action brisk as the Count of Monte Cristo tries to defeat a bullying dictator, and win a beautiful woman in the process. Also, look for Clayton Moore, TV's Lone Ranger, in one of his earliest roles!

programme.title: Dr. Christian Meets the Women (1940)
programme.desc: In the third installment of the six-part “Dr. Christian” series, Jean Hersholt (Grand Hotel) is featured as the eponymous medical professional. Things get interesting for the good doctor as an enigmatic, and possibly dangerous, “professor” rolls into town, promising instant weight loss to the local women. Follow this tale of Dr. Christian as he matches wits with Professor Kenneth Parker, played by screen veteran Rod La Roque (The Ten Commandments). This drama features fine work from Oscar nominated director William C. McGann and a cast that that includes the great Frank Albertson (Psycho).

programme.title: Mohawk (1956)
programme.desc: Kurt Newman (The Fly, Rocketship X­M) directed this bawdy tale of a love that was louder than war drums! With a cast that includes Scott Brady, Rita Gamm, and Neville Brand, the story takes place on a remote army post where an artist romances a trio of women, just as a vengeful settler turns the army and the local Iroquois tribe against each other. Film buffs might like to know that the cinematography for this feature is by four time Oscar nominee Karl Struss, who won an Academy Award in 1929 for his work on Sunrise.

programme.title: Crimes at the Dark House
programme.desc: A madman kills a man who has just inherited a large estate, then impersonates his victim to gain entrance to the estate so he can murder his enemies.

programme.title: The Hoodlum
programme.desc: One man must face his sociopathic brother. His brother, Vincent Lubeck, is a vicious ex-convict whose out on parole when he orchestrates an armored car robbery.

programme.title: Dementia 13 (1963)
programme.desc: Written and directed by a 24-year-old Francis Ford Coppola, "Dementia 13" centers on the dysfunctional Haloran family, who have converged at Haloran Castle to enact a morbid ritual in remembrance of Lady Haloran's (Ethne Dunn) deceased daughter, Kathleen (Barbara Dowling). Secrets shroud Kathleen's demise, and soon there is a mysterious interloper prowling the grounds with a big axe to grind. Genuinely engaging and well-photographed, "Dementia 13" is a bone-chilling horror classic sure to thrill horror enthusiasts and Coppola fans alike.

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 7
programme.desc: Guest starring Smothers Brothers, Diahann Carroll, and Richard Kiley in a series of skits including Carol and Lyle performing exercises, the Smothers Brothers doing a sketch, singing `John Henry' and joined by Carol on `Pretoria', guest Richard Kiley sings `The Impossible Dream', and guest Diahann Carroll sings `The Rules of the Road'.

programme.title: Season 23 Episode 91
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: Great Generals - Gen. George C. Marshall
programme.desc: Documentary on General George C. Marshall narrated by Walter Cronkite.

programme.title: Messiah of Evil
programme.desc: Starring a bevy of 1970s eye candy, including Anitra Ford, Joy Bang, and Marianna Hill, Messiah of Evil is about a young woman (Hill) whose search for her missing father brings her to a strange seaside town under the influence of a mysterious cult.

programme.title: The Brain That Wouldn't Die (1962)
programme.desc: While driving to his family’s country house, Dr. Bill Cortner (Jason Evers) and his fiancée, Jan Compton (Virginia Leith) get into a horrible car accident, leaving Jan decapitated. An expert in transplants, Dr. Cortner rushes to his lab with Jan’s severed head, and searches for a way to save his fiancée. Keeping her head alive in a liquid-filled tray, Dr. Cortner searches for a woman to murder in the hope that he may transplant Jan’s head onto a new body. His efforts lead to chaotic results. Written and directed by Joseph Green, this 1962 flick will be sure to keep you at the edge of your seat from beginning to end!

programme.title: Ghosts on the Loose (1943)
programme.desc: Bela Lugosi and the East Side Kids team up in this "spook comedy" from Monogram Pictures. The kids are trying to fix up a house for a newlywed couple, but find the place to be filled with secret panels, and even some strange men who seem to be lurking in the shadows. Look for the usual members of the gang, including Leo Gorcey as Mugs, and Huntz Hall as Gimpy, with the lovely Ava Gardner in her first speaking role. As the original ad campaign said, "It's Chill-arious!"

programme.title: Doomsday Machine
programme.desc: The crew aboard Project Astra, a space mission to Venus, witness the Earth being destroyed. Now they must ponder the repopulation of the human race.

programme.title: Money (1958)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big Producer
programme.desc: Obscene literature and pictures are spread among youngster at a school in Los Angeles. The supplier of this illegal stuff turns out to be a former film producer from the days of silent movies.

programme.title: Doomsday (1959)
programme.desc: Sentenced to be burned at the stake, a village woman in 17th Century Scotland shouts a curse that the eldest son of every generation to come of the Earl will die before the father.

programme.title: Black Light (1959)
programme.desc: Mike is hired to investigate when a police detective suspects a group of officers are being payed off.

programme.title: Denver McKee
programme.desc: Retired U.S. Deputy Marshall Denver McKee struggles to find the suspects responsible for stolen cattle and murdered ranchers.

programme.title: The Clampetts and the Dodgers
programme.desc: Jed and Jethro go golfing with Leo Durocher, coach of the Los Angeles Dodgers.

programme.title: The Case of the Royal Murder
programme.desc: As payment for solving a case, Holmes and Watson are invited to spend a weekend at an estate in the Balkans. Their vacation is cut short, however, when another guest, Prince Stefan, is poisoned.

programme.title: Death is a Red Balloon
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Al Brown Story
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: The New
programme.desc: A clerk named Stanley finds himself embroiled in the chaotic ongoings of New York City tourists inside an upscale hotel.

programme.title: Bud Takes Up the Dance
programme.desc: Bud prepares to take a girl to his first dance by learning dance steps from a 50 year old book.

programme.title: Speak Easily (1932)
programme.desc: The films Buster Keaton starred in at MGM during the 1930s are often dismissed as inferior to the work he did during the silent era, but the truth is that many of them are delightful. In Speak Easily he plays a shy professor who inherits some money, falls for a showgirl, and decides to become a Broadway producer. Jimmy Durante, and Hedda Hopper also star in this feature from director Edward Sedgwick, who happened to be behind some of Keaton’s best movies, including The Cameraman and Spite Marriage. This one might change your mind about the Keaton talkies!

programme.title: Springtime in the Sierras (1947)
programme.desc: Ads for this Roy Rogers classic roared HEAD FOR THE MUSICAL HILLS...ROY IS GUNNIN' FOR THRILLS! And thrills are what you'll get when you watch this fun, action packed B-Western from Republic Pictures. There's some great comic relief from Andy Devine and Chester Conklin, two of Hollywood's all-time greats. This old-fashioned shoot-'em-up was directed by William Witney, who would go on to direct many of television's top western sagas, including Bonanza, Wagon Train, and The Wild, Wild West.

programme.title: Abilene Town (1946)
programme.desc: Ablaze with guns and guts and glory! Randolph Scott headlines as a star studded cast in this yarn about battling homesteaders. Director Edwin L. Marin (Tall in the Saddle) spins this dramatic post-Civil War tale that takes place in the legendary cow town of Abilene, Kansas, coaxing fine performances from the likes of Ann Dvorak, Edgar Buchanan, Thonda Fleming, and Lloyd Bridges. Saddle up and hang on!

programme.title: Boy What a Girl (1947)
programme.desc: The scheming world of show business is the subject of this fascinating feature from Herald Pictures. Tim Moore, who went on to play “Kingfish” in the popular Amos & Andy show, heads a cast that includes Deek Watson and His Brown Dots, 'Big' Sid Catlett and his band, plus Ann Cornell and the International Jitterbugs. Also, look for legendary drummer Gene Krupa, who happened to visit the set, and was grabbed for a drumming cameo!

programme.title: Life, Animated
programme.desc: Nominated for the Academy Award for Best Documentary Feature and directed by Academy Award-winning director Roger Ross Williams, LIFE, ANIMATED is an emotional coming-of-age story that follows Owen Suskind, a young autistic man who learns how to communica

programme.title: Perfect Bid: The Contestant Who Knew Too Much
programme.desc: Ted Slauson is a Texas math genius who has spent the majority of his life memorizing the prize amounts on The Price is Right. THE PERFECT BID examines how Ted went from bidding to banned, and reveal his part in one of the biggest controversies in game sho

programme.title: Bluefin
programme.desc: Endangered giant bluefin tuna have returned to Prince Edward Island in surprising abundance after a complete disappearance from overfishing. But something strange is going on. Tuna no longer fear humans. A tale of epic stakes about an extraordinary specie

programme.title: Entrapped
programme.desc: The FBI claimed it exposed a dangerous group of men in a massive entrapment operation over an alleged plot to attack a U.S. Army base in New Jersey. But were they really terrorists?

programme.title: The Thousand Year Journey
programme.desc: "Routine is the enemy of time." Jedidiah Jenkins rides his bicycle from Oregon to Patagonia, the southern tip of South America, while expounding upon ideas that made him leave a job he loved for the open road.

programme.title: Elder
programme.desc: A Mormon missionary finds his world turned upside down when he falls in love with a handsome, Italian Communist. With original 8mm film Tom Clark recounts a love story on the coast of Italy.

programme.title: Gotta Groove Records
programme.desc: A short film on the history and resurgence of vinyl records from the perspective of an artist focused pressing plant in Cleveland, Ohio. A hero story about grit, manufacturing and warm tones.

programme.title: The Fate Of The Wild
programme.desc: A portrait of wild horse expert, Laura Leigh's personal and professional battles, set against the stark Nevada landscape.

As the bond develops between the two, their relationship takes an unexpected turn. Suddenly the past and the choices Gloria made as a young man become a stark reality.

programme.title: BIFL
programme.desc: Expectations, different shades of intimacy, & what it really means to love someone.

programme.title: Acrylic
programme.desc: A colorful neighborhood salon is threatened by a new addition. The pot is stirred by a local magazine competition and a long standing rivalry. Which salon has what it takes to win the grand prize?

programme.title: Ruined: A Hipster Ghost Story
programme.desc: Best friends Owen and Lucy land their dream flat, but the resident ghost makes their new lives a nightmare.

programme.title: Magic H8 Ball
programme.desc: Burned by a cheating boyfriend (and some mild chlamydia), a heartbroken pushover turns to a mysterious Magic 8 Ball for the answers. But as he starts giving into his impulses, he risks his hurt turning into hate-and losing all control.

programme.title: Louis Anderson: Big Baby Boomer
programme.desc: Veteran funny man Louie Anderson returns to the stage in this hilarious one hour stand up comedy special. Louie takes an unconventional and jovial look at his bad habits, pesky family members, and aging body.

programme.title: Ann
programme.desc: Ann is a feature film narrating the story of Ruben, a visual artist who has decided to abandon his tormented life by taking refuge within his own imagination; creating a world parallel to reality.

programme.title: Equality U
programme.desc: Equality U is a feature-length documentary following 34 young activists on the Soulforce Equality Ride. At some stops they're welcomed with open arms, at others they're arrested for trespassing or for simply attempting to open up a dialog. At every stop, they're connecting with young people who've often never met an openly gay, lesbian, bisexual or transgender person who is comfortable with who they are.

programme.title: Gaysians
programme.desc: An exploration of family, immigration and language through the voices of five queer and trans Asian-Americans from New York City. The subjects share stories about their families and the complicated histories that have shaped these relationships.

programme.title: For My Wife
programme.desc: A feature documentary chronicling the making of an activist. After the tragic death of her wife, Charlene Strong was thrust into the spotlight becoming a powerful voice ;for the equal rights of same-sex couples and their families.

programme.title: Good Monsters
programme.desc: Eric Stine, a biracial artist, embarks on a cross country journey of discovery, art, and inspiration. Good Monsters is a colorful film that shows Stine’s struggle to understand how his life and work have been affected by his estranged father.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S2 E3 | Victor, Lianna, and Enrique talk about conversion therapy, inclusion in Hollywood with casting director Yolanda Guillen, and living healthy through meal prepping with personal trainer Luis Suarez.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S2 E4 | Writer, Producer, and Director Stan Zimmerman (Golden Girls, Gilmore Girls) and actress Raquenel join us to discuss their LatinX retelling of The Diary of Anne Frank. Plus an interview with the first trans person to run for California state office, Ashlee Marie Preston. Also we discuss LGBTQ voter turnout and how it can improve.

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: Scrum
programme.desc: The lives of a self-assured Canadian jock, a rookie Irish backpacker and a stoic Japanese outsider change when they vie for a position in the grueling Bingham Cup.

programme.title: Denial
programme.desc: DENIAL is a documentary about electricity, identity, family, and about the many ways we lie to ourselves when faced with overwhelming facts. It is the story of a family coming to terms with complex personal truths against the backdrop of a global crisis.

programme.title: Davis Mallory | Heavy
programme.desc: The music video for "Heavy" by Davis Mallory featuring Blake Lieder and Daisha McBride. The music video for "Lifeline" by Davis Mallory featuring Allouche. The music video for "Little Victory" by Davis Mallory. A Look behind the scenes at Miami Pride 2021 with Davis Mallory

programme.title: Words
programme.desc: "Words" explores how people navigate gender & identity in the open & evolving landscape of NYC. Featuring exclusive interviews from a variety of artists, activists, icons & innovators. Powerful tribute to the language we use to shape our identities.

programme.title: South Beach On Heels
programme.desc: This award-winning documentary explores the on and offstage lives of eight hard-working drag entertainers. Follow Carmen Carrera, Latrice Royale, and other performers as they search for love, family, and acceptance in an industry built on big hair, big dreams and illusion.

programme.title: Still I Strive
programme.desc: The NACA orphanage in Phnom Penh, work to achieve one of the highest honors in Cambodian society, to perform before the Princess Bopha Devi. The children's epic performance is recreated as a cinematic adventure that parallels their harrowing backstories.

programme.title: Davis Mallory | Heavy

programme.title: Scales
programme.desc: S1 E1/2/3 | Meet Remy, Gavin, and David living in Atlanta finding balance in their lives. Remy has been single for quite some time, but an unexpected run in, could potentially change his fate./Remy is going to everyone for advice, including 17-year old Dakota Keller. Meanwhile, problems are brewing at home for Gavin and Sheila and David gets a rude awakening from a stranger./A revolving door can allow you to come in and out. In this case, Remy's house happens to be the revolving door, but someone ends up getting stuck. Remy and Sean must deal with their past. Sheila takes control of a situation and confronts Remy. Kevin’s sister, Gloria arrives with an update on Kevin’s progress.

programme.title: Scales
programme.desc: S1 E4/5/6 | Remy struggles to deal with the aftermath of his actions. Gavin and Sheila’s relationship continues to suffer. Meanwhile, David and Caleb find common ground with each other./Kevin returns home and Gloria expresses her doubts. Meanwhile, Dakota has news to share. David’s sister, Jade gives him encouragement to move forward. David reaches out to Caleb. Remy must face his past, for once and for all./In the season finale it’s a night of big reveals as the trio head to Caleb’s game night event. Ron has a question for Remy. It’s a game of all truths and not everyone will come out a winner.

programme.title: Gay Mean Girls
programme.desc: S1 E1-2 | Lucy is a “very good ally” who stares at her best friend Miranda…. a lot. They hatch a plan to start Gay Prom Royalty together to promote equality at their school. Miranda pays Lucy a visit on a day off from school. We get a glimpse into Lucy’s home life.

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.title: Gina Yashere: Laughing To America
programme.desc: Filmed live in San Francisco, CA, UK's premier black female comedian, Gina Yashere, has come to America! Her unique take on being a cultural insider and outsider never fails to raise the roof as she gives us her take on the news gripping the nation.

programme.title: Becoming Queen
programme.desc: There has never been a band like Queen, and there never will again. Take a twenty year ride with the people who knew them best.

programme.title: Love V Kentucky
programme.desc: An intimate account of how two Kentucky attorneys with no background in civil rights navigate their passionate opponents, wrangle their reluctant allies, and convince the U.S. Supreme Court to rewrite our nation’s definition of marriage.

programme.title: Jonathan's Kitchen
programme.desc: S1 E6 | Marianne Tshihamba joins me to create a vegan take on one of my favorite side dishes.

programme.title: Jonathan's Kitchen
programme.desc: S1 E7 | Danny Kaylor-Hawkins joins me to prepare a quiet dinner for our husbands.

programme.title: Coming of Age in Cherry Grove
programme.desc: Founded in 1869, Cherry Grove (Fire Island, NY) is considered by most to be the first openly LGBTQ community in the United States. It has become known as one of the most accepting resort communities in the world – a place where you can not only discover who you are, but also freely experiment with who or what (gender) you may want to become. Cherry Grove is also known for the famous “INVASION” – an annual ritual that takes place every July 4th as a celebration of gender acceptance. This film tells the stories of a variety of long-term residents and what they find so wonderful about life in Cherry Grove.

programme.title: Were You Gay In High School?
programme.desc: Two queer women recall their awkward, closeted high school days of kissing boys and straight-girl crushes.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S2 E5 | We're joined by Eric and Jose of the Homo Homies Podcast, founder of Marianella luxury soaps David Foote, and we discuss depression amongst LGBTQ youth.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S2 E6 | We're joined by LGBTQ activist Queen Victoria Ortega, music sensation Georgel, and we find out if adopting a pet can help strengthen relationships.

programme.title: Little Miss Westie
programme.desc: If Ren could go back in time before she was four, she would tell her parents that she wasn’t happy living as a boy. Now, Ren is about to take part in a rite of passage for their community in West Haven, CT as the first out transgirl to compete in the Little Miss Westie Pageant. Coaching her through the competition: Her older brother Luca, who previously took part in the pageant when he lived as a girl. Gender dynamics evolve in front of the viewer’s eyes while two transgender siblings explore who they are in this intimate portrait.

programme.title: The Billionaire
programme.desc: A gender-swapped independent film adaptation of George Bernard Shaw's classic play 'The Millionairess', transposed into a contemporary context of Gay Marriage and Asexuality, THE BILLIONAIRE follows a haughty and prudish young billionaire's quest for love, despite all the odds. The film is a throwback to Classic Hollywood films, stylistically and tonally.

programme.title: No Gender! The Queer Life Of An Intersex Manga Artist
programme.desc: Up until age 30, Sho Arai lived as a woman, but was found to be intersex after chromosome testing.

programme.title: Carmín Tropical
programme.desc: Mabel, a muxe, returns home to her village in Oaxaca, Mexico to find her friend's killer.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: Culture Q is the world’s first weekly queer-centric news series brought to you by the leading global queer streaming network, Revry. This innovative, weekly news series creatively features entertainment, pop culture, lifestyle and political news with wit and insightfully nuanced perspectives. Emphasizing the queer millieu, Culture Q stands to be the leading, weekly forum for boundary-pushing discussions and commentary. Hosted by digital news influencer pioneers, Shira Lazar and Andy Lalwani of the highly successful What’s Trending, Culture Q will feature an ever-changing cavalcade of guests who help capture that X-factor which defines queer culture.

programme.title: Out On Stage
programme.desc: Out On Stage is THE absolutely hilarious and one-of-a-kind, originally produced comedy hosted by Zach Noe Towers! See OUT Magazine's "1 of the 10 comedians to watch in 2018," the comedian that Sarah Silverman calls, "So, SO, SO Funny" and 17 other top-rated Gay and Lesbian stand-up comedians discuss taboo subjects as only they can!

programme.title: The Drag Roast Of Heklina
programme.desc: S1 E1 | Check your political correctness at the door and bring your finest, biggest wig for a raucous, no-holds-barred roast of one of San Francisco’s favorite larger-than-life drag personalities, the one and only Heklina—aka Stefan Grygelko. This Revry Original special features such roasters as Jackie Beat, Julie Brown (Clueless), Peaches Christ, Sister Roma, Alaska Thunderf*ck, and Jinkx Monsoon.

programme.title: Barbelle
programme.desc: S1 E7-10 | Alice and Veronica head to the studio to work on the new album. After Karen informs Alice that Lulu will no longer be working on the new album, Alice realizes this might be the end of her and Lulu's relationship. Veronica attempts to win back Alice by writing the perfect song. Her writer's block leads to a downward spiral of shoplifting and booze only hours before she is set to accompany Brooklyn to prom. Alice confronts Veronica about her poor choices. Veronica wakes up to find The Ghost of Girlfriend's Past waiting to take her on a Dickensian journey through her past. Alice accompanies Brooklyn to her prom in Veronica's stead. Lulu shows up to the prom unannounced, as does another surprise guest.↵

programme.title: RABBIT WOMAN
programme.desc: A China-born state employee discovers corruption within the Argentinian police force and bravely sets out to bring an end to its corrupt ties to the Chinese mafia. While on the run from the criminals, she discovers a bizarre animal experiment involving rabbits that perversely may hold the key to her success.

programme.title: OMNIVORES
programme.desc: A prestigious journalist accepts an undercover writing assignment addressing the recent emergence of "clandestine restaurants," one of which holds secret gatherings where diners feast on human flesh in exchange for large sums of money. What started as a simple job may just end in a bloody nightmare.

programme.title: The Maid
programme.desc: When her mistress brings on another servant to help with the chores, a bitter and introverted maid wreaks havoc on the household.

programme.title: CONTRACORRIENTE
programme.desc: Miguel is a fisherman in a tiny Peruvian village where traditions run deep. He is married to the lovely Mariela and about to be a father, but has a secret love affair with Santiago, a painter, who is ostracized by the town because he's gay. After a tragic accident occurs, Miguel must choose between sentencing Santiago to eternal torment or doing right by him and, in turn, revealing their relationship to Mariela and the entire village.

programme.title: DIA NARANJA
programme.desc: Three Latin American women from different backgrounds see their fantasies about the future give way to anxiety as they are hit with the same shocking news: they are pregnant. A colorful, vivacious look at the excitement and drama that often accompanies the prospect of motherhood.

Cannaisseurship: Appreciate all that went into this medicine, its taste, smell, feel and how it enhances your everyday life. Creation, inspiration, relaxation, reflection. programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: S8E11 - Prague
programme.desc: We'll visit beautifully preserved Prague to experience its massive castle, evocative Jewish Quarter, thrilling history, infectious music...and perhaps the best beer in Europe.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: Running of the Bulls
programme.desc: The Festival of San Fermin in Pamplona, Spain is a deeply rooted celebration of traditional and folkloric events, including the Running of the Bulls. Experience the incredible energy each morning for eight consecutive days as thousands of people run ahead of six, 2,000-pound charging bulls.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: France's Burgundy and Loire Regions
programme.desc: The Burgundy region boasts top French wines, romantic canals, Romanesque churches, and world-renowned French cuisine. We base in the small town of Beaune and learn about its history of exceptional winemaking. Add a wondrous hot-air balloon ride over the verdant Loire Valley to the itinerary.

programme.title: Berlin
programme.desc: With world-class cultural sites, dynamic new architecture and unstoppable energy, Berlin is a city on the move. We visit the museums - the ancient treasures of the Pergamon and the Egyptian museum, German Expressionism at the Neue Nationalgalerie and the newly designed Jewish Museum.

programme.title: S7E8 - London: Historic and Dynamic
programme.desc: In London, we’ll ponder royal tombs in Westminster Abbey, discover treasures in the British Library, enjoy the vibrant evening scene in Soho, uncover Churchill’s secret WWII headquarters, and straddle the Prime Meridian at Greenwich.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Tahiti and Bora Bora
programme.desc: For sheer tropical splendor, the islands of Tahiti and Bora Bora stand alone. Hyper blue lagoons, white-sand beaches, fish of every shape, size, and color, as well as a generous and welcoming people make these islands key destinations for travelers from around the world.

programme.title: Polynesia
programme.desc: Experience Polynesia’s rich sea life, crystal blue waters, and vibrant cultures. Tour the diverse reefs of the coral, sea turtle rehabilitation centers, and the many islands and atolls. Participate in the oyster-cultivation process at the major pearl farm, and tour dramatic Marquesas Islands.

programme.title: Montreal
programme.desc: Two of the most unique cities in the world are just north of New England. Here you will find brie, pate, jewel box-patisseries, and “s’il vous plait” right along with bagels, maple syrup, hockey, delis, and bocce ball. Those who forged Montreal and Quebec City braved much to see them flourish.

programme.title: Nova Scotia & Newfoundland
programme.desc: From the charming fishing towns of Nova Scotia to the vast wilderness of Newfoundland, explore the last great open spaces of Eastern North America. A touch of New England, a dash of Germany, here a British fort, there an Irish brogue, the area was peopled by the descendants of hardy colonists.

programme.title: Food, Drink, & Culture
programme.desc: In Istanbul’s Spice Market, brown-gold paprika is carefully molded into pyramids. Cinnamon, cumin, ginger, and cardamom infuse the air. From haggis in Scotland to soba and tea in Japan, from asada in Argentina to bibimbap in Korea, food and drink help illustrate the culture and people of a location.

programme.title: Asian Cities
programme.desc: From the world’s largest city, Tokyo, to the colorful chaos of Delhi, and from the modern miracle of Seoul to the teeming streets of Bangkok, this is your passport to the high-tech marvels and back-street secrets of four of the world’s most amazing cities Asian Cities.

programme.title: From Myanmar to Scotland
programme.desc: Biodiversity is a central component to the successful operation of Earth’s natural systems. Meet people from Haiti, Myanmar, Honduras, Kenya, Canada, and Scotland who spend time and energy securing healthy local environmental regulations.

programme.title: Unfair Game
programme.desc: Zambia and Eswatini (formerly Swaziland) represent two divergent strategies on environmentalism. Meet people from both countries and learn of the successes, failures, and sacrifices they experienced seeking environmental justice.

programme.title: Italy's Via Cassia

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.desc: Lake Mohave spans over 67 miles along the Nevada and Arizona border and is one of the best lakes to fish in the Southwest. Offering many species, including bluegill, channel catfish, striped bass, smallmouth bass, and largemouth bass. Shea McIntee and the crew take a trip to Lake Mohave and see what it's all about.

programme.title: Angling Buzz - The Quality of Fishing Today
programme.desc: This is episode FIVE of AnglingBuzz TV 2017. In this episode, we talk about the quality of fishing today, and why it's better than it's ever been. These are the "Good Old Days" of fishing!

programme.title: Angling Buzz - Seasonal Peaks
programme.desc: This is episode FOUR of AnglingBuzz TV 2017. In this episode, we explore some of the hot seasonal peaks going on right now across the Upper Midwest, including where to find fish and how to catch them!

programme.title: Lindner's Angling Edge - Junk Fishin' Bass
programme.desc: James Lindner and Jeremy Smith break out the bass gear for an early-summer run on a Midwestern natural lake and find epic bites in shallow-water junk.

programme.title: Lindner's Angling - Search Bait Bass
programme.desc: Al Lindner and bait designer Mark Fisher go on the prowl for post-turnover bass while putting a brand-new bait to the test.

programme.title: Wired2Fish - 5 Tips For Texas-Rigged Worms
programme.desc: Jacob Wheeler talks about the importance of hook and weight selection and his top 2 retrieval methods when fishing Texas-rigged ribbontail worms offshore.

programme.title: Brauer Bass Battles: Lake Amistad Largemouths (Part 2)
programme.desc: The Brauers compete to see who can best figure out how to catch largemouth bass on Lake Amistad, Texas / Mexico. Day Two.

programme.title: Hank Parker Outdoors: Custom lake fishing
programme.desc: Hank and close friend/business partner, Keith Kelly return to Hank's premiere signature lake. Designed & built five years ago, this custom body of water proves to be a fishery like no other.

programme.title: Hank Parker Outdoors: Singing in the rain
programme.desc: Flooded conditions on Lake Champlain has Hank looking for some clear water in areas he's never fished before.

programme.title: Hobie Fishing - Kayak Fishing for Big Bass on the Brazos River
programme.desc: Have you ever done a float kayak fishing trip? In this episode of Hobie Outdoor Adventures, friends meet up for a 10-mile float down the Brazos River in Texas and land some giant bass from our Hobie fishing kayaks.

programme.title: Hobie Fishing - Ike at His Best Featuring MLF Star Mike Iaconelli
programme.desc: Whether it’s redfish in the bayous of Louisiana, halibut off Southern California, or smallmouth bass in the rivers of the northeast, Bass Pro angler Mike Iaconelli always has fun out of his Hobie fishing kayak.

programme.title: Pro Vs Joe - Camera Crew Madness
programme.desc: Brent Chapman’s Pro Vs Joe Camera Crew Madness

programme.title: Pro Vs Joe - South Florida Canals1
programme.desc: Brent Chapman’s Pro Vs Joe South Florida Canals1

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - The Magdalena Bay Experience, Part Two
programme.desc: One of the best parts of traveling is the pleasant surprises that come along every trip. In last week's episode, Shea McIntee and the crew had a remarkable day of Marlin fishing in Madalena Bay. Now we find out Madalena Bay doesn't only have fantastic offshore fishing, it also has inshore fishing that is out of this world. Shea's captain takes us to some of his favorite spots to catch Red Snapper, Snook, Corbina, and a fish we have never seen before, Palometa.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake
programme.desc: Going camping and trout fishing in the Sierras is one of our favorite things to do. For the first time, Shea McIntee and the crew head down to South Lake Bishop. What makes this trip unique is that we get to fish with some good friends.

programme.title: Angling Buzz - Why America Loves Crappy
programme.desc: This is episode THREE of AnglingBuzz TV 2017. In this episode, we tackle one of America's favorite fish: the crappie! This is a deep dive into how to find crappies during the spring of the year, and how to catch them!

programme.title: Angling Buzz - Walleye Mastery
programme.desc: This is episode two of AnglingBuzz TV 2017. In this episode, we dive deep into what it means to be a 'Walleye Master', from the techniques and presentations to the nitty gritty of fish location.

programme.title: Lindner's Angling - Coho Mania

programme.title: Animation: Audi RS e-tron GT – Electric Quattro and Recuperation
programme.desc: The e-tron GT quattro and the RS e-tron GT usually drive with electric all-wheel drive, only the “efficiency” mode of the Audi drive select dynamic handling system prioritizing the front-wheel drive. In event of a slippery road surface, high power requirements, or fast cornering, the electric motor for rear-wheel drive is also activated here, and around five times faster than with a mechanical quattro drivetrain. The electric all-wheel drive regulates the drive torque distribution between the axles – continuously, fully variably, and within a few thousandths of a second. The quattro principle of the four-wheel drive that Audi introduced to the market more than 40 years ago presents itself on a new, fascinating technological level. When the driver releases the right-hand pedal, the drive usually switches to sailing, allowing the gran turismo to glide with elegance and efficiency. By contrast, the car recuperates in overrun mode in the “dynamic” mode of Audi drive select. - Audi RS e-tron GT: Combined electric power consumption in kWh/100 km (62.1 mi)*: 20.2–19.3 (NEDC), 22.5–20.6 (WLTP); combined CO2 emissions in g/km (g/mi)*: 0 - Information on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions as well as efficiency classes in ranges depending on the tires and alloy wheel rims used.

programme.title: Audi Annual Press Conference 2020
programme.desc: 2020 was dominated by a global pandemic and great upheaval, which therefore shifted the focus even more strongly to the question of responsible actions. As part of the automotive industry, we are responsible for our employees and customers, for stable economic growth, and for a sustainable business model. Despite – or precisely because of – the current challenges, we are in a position where we can make a big difference. At Audi, we see ambitious climate targets, the paradigm shift toward software, and the impetus created by new competitors as an opportunity to play an active part in shaping the future of mobility. Our Board of Management team, which has been active in a new constellation for about a year, will provide an overview on how Audi handled the unusual year of 2020 and on which future topics we have our sights firmly set.

programme.desc: Speaking on centre stage at Web Summit 2019, Lilium CEO Daniel Wiegand and Tencent's CXO David Wallerstein discuss the Lilium Jet and the potential it has to address some of the planet’s biggest challenges, from climate change to regional mobility. As well as explaining how Lilium could expand your ‘Radius of Life’, the talk also covers many of the challenges ahead, like noise and safety, while explaining how Lilium can make the service available at a surprisingly affordable price.

programme.title: Electrified - The Current State of Electric Vehicles
programme.desc: Chelsea Sexton, Paul Scott, Forth Mobility, and several owners come together to discuss how electric cars have evolved and where we currently are in the state of this developing technology. It covers issues and experiences related to charging, battery degradation, and range anxiety, along with detailed explanations of charging levels, types of electric vehicles, and the future of hydrogen. - This film prepares viewers with the knowledge needed for properly assessing vehicle options, along with considerations for charging, and knowledge about what they may need to know before making a purchase.

programme.title: NIO Defined

programme.title: Astypalea: Smart, Sustainable Island
programme.desc: Astypalea up until now is probably only known to insiders. The small island is located in the Aegean Sea, it belongs to Greece and is especially known for its butterflies. This is likely to change in the future: Astypalea will become a model for smart, emission-free mobility. The island wants to prove that a purely electric transport system is already possible today – without any restrictions on the mobility of its inhabitants. We explain the details.

programme.title: The Porsche Taycan Goes Golfing

programme.title: Audi Annual Press Conference 2020
programme.desc: 2020 was dominated by a global pandemic and great upheaval, which therefore shifted the focus even more strongly to the question of responsible actions. As part of the automotive industry, we are responsible for our employees and customers, for stable economic growth, and for a sustainable business model. Despite – or precisely because of – the current challenges, we are in a position where we can make a big difference. At Audi, we see ambitious climate targets, the paradigm shift toward software, and the impetus created by new competitors as an opportunity to play an active part in shaping the future of mobility. Our Board of Management team, which has been active in a new constellation for about a year, will provide an overview on how Audi handled the unusual year of 2020 and on which future topics we have our sights firmly set.

programme.title: Laura McKenzie's Traveler
programme.desc: Malta- - Laura visits a re-enactment of La Guardia, which represents a military performance that used to take place in the time of the Knights of St. John. Plus, the walled city of Mdina then Valletta Gozo, The Blue Grotto, St. Paul’s Catacombs, and the Temple of Hagar Qim. Finally, Laura rounds out her trip with an excursion to Ggantia, the oldest free-standing structure in the world.

programme.title: The Bay- The Beginning
programme.desc: Episode 4- - Much to Sara’s surprise, event planner Sofia Madison, the wife of Mayor Jack Madison, arrives at the Garrett estate for Brian and Zoey’s wedding. Zoey’s father Harold also shows up in town for the wedding and sets a surprised and uninformed Zoey off. An adulterous Marly and her lover Manny Ramos are interrupted when Manny’s sister Janice unexpectedly turns up needing his help and revealing some shocking news. Lee confronts Commissioner Lex Martin about Sara and Lex’s affair. Later, Pete returns to Bay City and confronts Sara. Lee discovers his stepson Brian is keeping secrets as Zoey has a change of heart.

programme.desc: Food Fun, Fifty Shades of Rope, and Crazy, Crazy Cards- - Simon Pierro works more of his techno magic on Scorpion star Ari Stidham. programme.desc: “Origin of the Universe”: theories about how the whole thing started! “Chicago Ghosts”: weird hauntings in the Windy City. “Past Life Regression”: do we live more than one life? Actual on-camera regression session.

programme.title: Gay Positive
programme.desc: Gay Positive educates viewers about the controversial ban on queer men donating blood in the USA. The film captures opinions of people from all walks of life, asking, If you were in need of blood would you take it from a queer? Organizations are forced to reject healthy individuals from donating. During the filming of this documentary, Mexico and the UK lifted their ban, while the FDA insists it remain. Through insightful conversations with Laverne Cox, Rutanya Alda, Blanche Baker, Jim Colucci, Frank DeCaro, Trapper Felides, Tiago Grade, Carly Hughes, Chelsey Keding, Yetta Kurland, Lisa Lampanelli, Vincent Leggett, Danny Logan, Dave McRee, Anthony Lee Medina, Eric Millegan, Kaitlin Monte, Tym Moss, Garry Novikoff, Athena Reich, and Justin Luke Zirilli; Gay Positive raises public awareness on the potential benefits of lifting the ban.

programme.title: Political Animals
programme.desc: Political Animals celebrates the legendary civil rights victories of four trailblazing California state politicians: Carole Migden, Sheila Keuhl, Jackie Goldberg, and Christine Kehoe. Fierce and unrelenting, these courageous women toppled a partisan majority and emerged victors to pass historic legislation for social justice and LGBT+ equality. It was a hard fight – filled with vehemently heated debates and hateful insults hurled by opponents. Today, the message behind Political Animals is more important than ever as the current political theatre unfurls around the globe. These inspiring biographies further reveal the critical importance for public resistance at the local level to pressure lawmakers to enact difficult change. Political Animals is a clear call to action for a new era of greater democratic participation. We invite you to follow in the footsteps of these historic leaders and become the next pioneering political animal!

programme.desc: Known as the first openly gay rock star, Jobriath’s reign was a brief two years. Done in by over-hyped publicity, shunned by the gay community, and dismissed by critics, Jobriath retreated to the Chelsea Hotel, where he died forgotten, one of the earliest casualties of AIDS. But years later, new fans discover his music, and acts such as The Pet Shop Boys, Def Leppard, and Morrissey cite him as an influence. Experience the heartbreaking, unbelievable story of the one, the only, Jobriath.

programme.title: TransMilitary
programme.desc: The 2018 SXSW Audience Award-winning feature film debut by Gabriel Silverman, Fiona Dawson, & Jamie Coughlin, TransMilitary follows the Emmy-nominated short film Transgender, at War and in Love. Around 15,500 transgender people serve in the U.S. military (notably the largest transgender employer in the U.S.), where they must conceal their gender identity because military policies ban their service. TransMilitary chronicles the lives of four individuals (Senior Airman Logan Ireland, Corporal Laila Villanueva, Captain Jennifer Peace & First Lieutenant El Cook) defending their country’s freedom while fighting for their own. They put their careers and their families’ livelihoods on the line by coming out as transgender to top brass officials in the Pentagon in hopes of attaining the equal right to serve. The ban was lifted in 2016, but with President Trump now trying to reinstate it, their futures hang in the balance once again.

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

The Queen of Ireland is a documentary that follows drag queen Panti Bliss: part glamorous aunt, part Jessica Rabbit, she's a wittily incisive performer with charisma to burn who is widely regarded as one of the best drag queens in the world. Created by Rory O’Neill, Panti is also an accidental activist and in her own words ‘a court jester, whose role is to say the un-sayable’. In recent years, Rory has become a figurehead for LGBT rights in Ireland and since the 2014 scandal around Pantigate, his fight for equality and against homophobia has become recognised across the world. programme.desc: Equality U is a feature-length documentary following 34 young activists on the Soulforce Equality Ride. At some stops they're welcomed with open arms, at others they're arrested for trespassing or for simply attempting to open up a dialog. At every stop, they're connecting with young people who've often never met an openly gay, lesbian, bisexual or transgender person who is comfortable with who they are.

programme.title: J.S. Bach: Organ Concerts
programme.desc: Per rendere omaggio a Johann Sebastian Bach che ha servito per 27 anni come "maestro di cappella" nella chiesa di San Tommaso a Lipsia, l'organista Ullrich Böhme dà un concerto sul nuovo organo della chiesa: una replica del modello storico che suonava Bach.

programme.title: Jakub Jozef Orlinski- Il Pomo D'Oro
programme.desc: Il controtenore polacco Jakub Józef Orlinski si è guadagnato in breve tempo la reputazione di cantante dalla sorprendente padronanza vocale e dall'audacia scenica. Questo concerto riflette la tanto attesa uscita del suo primo album, Anima Sacra, un recital di arie sacre del XVIII secolo recentemente riscoperte con il gruppo barocco Il Pomo d'oro.

programme.title: Esa-Pekka Salonen - Joyce DiDonato
programme.desc: Dal 1994, il Festival di Verbier è un luogo d'incontro musicale internazionale nella Svizzera francese. Grandi artisti vi si esibiscono ogni anno davanti a un pubblico fedele. Nel 2015, il Festival accoglie il brillante mezzosoprano americano Joyce DiDonato. Eseguirà Summer Nights, Op. 7 di Hector Berlioz, sotto la direzione di Esa-Pekka Solonen, il famoso direttore d'orchestra finlandese. Si tratta di sei melodie francesi su bellissime poesie di Théophile Gautier da La Comédie de la mort.

programme.title: Daniel Oren & Saioa Hernandez - ORW
programme.desc: L'affascinante soprano spagnolo Saioa Hernández, con la sua voce potente e ammaliante, interpreta le famose arie d'opera italiane in concerto. Questo spettacolo ci permette di apprezzare il bel canto "l'arte del canto lirico" utilizzato nelle opere dal XVII secolo. Valorizzando le capacità tecniche dei cantanti, a volte a scapito dell'espressione scenica, la voce vola come fosse un uccellino.

programme.title: Danza Contemporánea de Cuba
programme.desc: Cuba non è solo famosa per i suoi sigari, ma anche per la sua vita culturale molto ricca - dove la danza gioca un ruolo importante. Nel film di Patrick Lauze, la compagnia Danza - Contemporánea de Cuba, creata nel 1959, esegue tre danze sacre al Teatro Nazionale Alicia Alonso all'Avana, Cuba.

A. Mozart al Festival di Lucerna nell'estate 2012. Le voci solenni di Anna Prohaska (soprano), Sara Mingardo (contralto), Maximilian Schmitt (tenore) e René Pape (basso) esprimono la bellezza e la profondità di questo capolavoro.

programme.title: The Nutcracker - Mariinsky
programme.desc: Ed è proprio sul palco del Mariinsky di San Pietroburgo che, nel 1892, è stato creato il capolavoro di Tchaïkovski: lo Schiaccianoci. Sullo stesso palcoscenico, 120 anni dopo, l’orchestra del medesimo teatro, sotto alla bacchetta del maestro Valery Gergiev, accompagnata dal prestigioso balletto del teatro Mariinsky, ne offre una versione che non potrebbe essere più fiabesca.

programme.title: Leonidas Kavakos And Yuja Wang
programme.desc: Due degli artisti più emblematici del Festival di Verbier interpretano insieme le opere di Brahms in un ricco concerto di musica da camera. Acclamato all'unanimità dal mondo della musica classica dal 1985, quando fece scalpore diventando il più giovane vincitore del prestigioso Concorso Sibelius, il violinista greco Leonidas Kavakos combina in questo concerto il suo virtuosismo con quello della pianista Yuja Wang, un'artista affermata a soli 26 anni.

programme.desc: Un’ora con i migliori artisti del momento: Barenboim, Repin, Lang Lang…

programme.title: W. A. Mozart: Piano Concerto No.19
programme.desc: Qui il grande pianista Radu Lupu esegue il Concerto n. 19 in FA maggiore di Mozart, accompagnato dall'orchestra della Deutsche Kammerphilharmonie sotto alla direzione di David Zinman. Un'opera magistrale, composta per la cerimonia di incoronazione dell'imperatore austriaco Leopoldo II nel 1790.

programme.title: Daniel Barenboim - W. E. Orchestra
programme.desc: Orchestra di portata molto simbolica, la West-Eastern Divan Orchestra è stata creata grazie allo slancio del direttore israelo-argentino Daniel Barenboim e del critico letterario Edward Saïd. Riunisce tutti i giovani musicisti israeliani e dei paesi arabi vicini - come ad esempio la Siria, la Giordania o i territori palestinesi - con un unico obiettivo: gettare dei ponti fra le comunità attraverso la musica. In diretta dalla Philharmonie di Berlino nel 2006, interpretano l’imponente nona sinfonia di Beethoven.

programme.title: Lang Lang - Piano Recital
programme.desc: La scelta di Lang Lang per la musica e la modalità di presentazione ha affermato la sua sensibilità del XXI° secolo rendendo al tempo stesso omaggio ai suoi precedenti pianistici e ai suoi mentori. Non è stato certo un caso che abbia suonato Wanderer Fantasy di Schubert, la prima opera che il suo insegnante del Curtis Institute, Gary Graffman, aveva registrato e usato per concludere il concerto delle Réminiscences Du Don Juan de Mozart di Liszt, associato ai più grandi virtuosi del pianoforte.

programme.title: Vox Luminis: Handel in Versailles
programme.desc: È nella sontuosa Cappella Reale di Versailles che il gruppo Vox Luminis porta Georg Friedrich Handel sotto i riflettori. Specializzato nel repertorio barocco inglese, italiano e tedesco, il gruppo Vox Luminis, sotto la direzione di Lionel Meunier, esegue con leggerezza e raffinatezza due salmi, un'opera lirica e un oratorio.

programme.title: Bach and Philippe Herreweghe
programme.desc: Philippe Herreweghe, direttore d'orchestra e del coro belga, è specializzato in musica antica, in particolare quella di Johann Sebastian Bach. Qui dirige il Collegium Vocal de Gand, che ha fondato nel 1970. A Parigi, nella chiesa barocca di Saint-Roch, le sontuose voci di Grace Davidson (soprano), Damien Guillon (controtenore), Thomas Hobbs (tenore) e Peter Kooij (basso) risuonano in un programma religioso dedicato al Natale.

programme.title: Paolo Arrivabeni - ORW
programme.desc: L'opera è sinonimo di cantanti. Eppure l'orchestra sinfonica gioca un ruolo cruciale in queste opere musicali e teatrali. L'Orchestre Royal de Wallonie - Liège, sotto la direzione di Paolo Arrivabeni, ci introduce quindi alla ricchezza della musica strumentale di alcune opere.

programme.title: PUCCINI by Julien Lestel Company
programme.desc: Le eroine del compositore Giacomo Puccini erano quasi sempre condannate a un tragico destino. Qui vengono portate sul palco accompagnate dalle arie più belle. Questa coreografia è un omaggio all'opera, e in particolare all'illustre compositore scomparso.

programme.title: Ivan Fischer: Schubert and Bruckner
programme.desc: Sotto la direzione magistrale di Iván Fischer, l'orchestra esegue due opere incompiute del periodo romantico. Questo intenso programma, eseguito con sentimento e profondità dalla Budapest Festival Orchestra, ci immerge immediatamente in un abisso emotivo.

programme.title: The Magic Flute - Simon Rattle
programme.desc: Il Flauto magico è l'opera finale di Mozart. Un racconto meraviglioso, una favola popolare o un racconto che marca il periodo della sua maturità, la storia della regina della notte, il principe Tamino, il vanaglorioso uccellatore Papageno e il suo flauto magico, ha lasciato il segno nei cuori e nelle menti. Accompagnato dalla prestigiosa Berliner Philharmoniker Orchestra sotto alla direzione di Simon Rattle, il direttore Robert Carsen rivisita questo classico con un tocco raffinato attraverso una profonda riflessione sulla vita e sulla morte.

programme.title: Beethoven - Daniel Barenboim
programme.desc: Qui l'illustre direttore d'orchestra Daniel Barenboim suona e dirige i cinque concerti di Beethoven con l'Orchestra della Staatskapelle di Berlino in occasione del suo 65° compleanno. Il Concerto n. 5 in MI bemolle maggiore, noto come "L'Imperatore", vede il maestro rivoluzionare la forma con un primo movimento lungo seicento battute. Un'improvvisazione messa per iscritto?

programme.title: Denis Matsuev at Concertgebouw
programme.desc: Il pianista russo Denis Matsuev, uno dei più grandi virtuosi del suo strumento, si esibisce qui in un recital solista sul palcoscenico del Concertgebouw di Amsterdam. In programma ci sono le Stagioni di Tchaikovsky, un classico della musica russa per celebrare il 175° compleanno del compositore nel 2015, e un'altra opera romantica: La Kreisleriana di Schumann. Egli esegue anche l'impressionante e virtuosistico "Tre Movimenti di Petrushka" di Stravinsky.

programme.title: G. Puccini: Tosca - Simon Rattle
programme.desc: Basata su un'opera teatrale di Victorien Sardou, l'opera Tosca ha conquistato il pubblico sin dalla sua uscita nel 1900. Questo dramma verista è sublimato dalla composizione virtuosa di Puccini. - Sotto la direzione di Sir Simon Rattle, la storia d'amore di Floria Tosca e Mario Cavaradossi si svolge e viene messa alla prova dal tirannico capo della polizia Scarpia, che governa Roma. In questa produzione, il famoso tenore argentino Marcelo Álvarez trascende la scena, accompagnato dalla sublime Kristine Opolais nel ruolo dell'eroina.

programme.title: Lang Lang - Debut at Carnegie Hall
programme.desc: Anche se Lang Lang aveva a malapena festeggiato il suo 21° compleanno all'epoca di questo concerto, il suo portfolio vanta già una serie impressionante di apparizioni internazionali di alto profilo. La sua selezione di apertura, le Variazioni "Abegg" di Schumann, figura nel debutto alla Carnegie Hall di Yevgeny Kissin nel 1990, mentre la sonata in DO maggiore di Haydn è apparsa due volte durante il celebre debutto dei cinque concerti di Sviatoslav Richter al Carnegie nel 1960.

Valorizzando le capacità tecniche dei cantanti, a volte a scapito dell'espressione scenica, la voce vola come fosse un uccellino.

programme.title: Leonidas Kavakos And Yuja Wang
programme.desc: Due degli artisti più emblematici del Festival di Verbier interpretano insieme le opere di Brahms in un ricco concerto di musica da camera. Acclamato all'unanimità dal mondo della musica classica dal 1985, quando fece scalpore diventando il più giovane vincitore del prestigioso Concorso Sibelius, il violinista greco Leonidas Kavakos combina in questo concerto il suo virtuosismo con quello della pianista Yuja Wang, un'artista affermata a soli 26 anni.

programme.title: Denis Matsuev at Concertgebouw
programme.desc: Il pianista russo Denis Matsuev, uno dei più grandi virtuosi del suo strumento, si esibisce qui in un recital solista sul palcoscenico del Concertgebouw di Amsterdam. In programma ci sono le Stagioni di Tchaikovsky, un classico della musica russa per celebrare il 175° compleanno del compositore nel 2015, e un'altra opera romantica: La Kreisleriana di Schumann. Egli esegue anche l'impressionante e virtuosistico "Tre Movimenti di Petrushka" di Stravinsky.

programme.title: Beethoven - Daniel Barenboim
programme.desc: Qui l'illustre direttore d'orchestra Daniel Barenboim suona e dirige i cinque concerti di Beethoven con l'Orchestra della Staatskapelle di Berlino in occasione del suo 65° compleanno. programme.title: Beethoven: Ode to Joy
programme.desc: In occasione del 20° anniversario dello Young Euro Classic - un festival che riunisce giovani musicisti promettenti provenienti dai 28 paesi dell'Unione europea - la European Union Youth Orchestra esegue una nuova versione della Sinfonia n. 9 op. 125 di Ludwig van Beethoven. L'ultimo tempo di questa sinfonia, composta nel 1823, è un vero successo della musica classica. È il preludio dell'Inno alla gioia, che dal 1970 è divenuto l'inno europeo suonato in occasione delle nelle cerimonie ufficiali.
